<br>
On the Rathe at my play times the spiroc tree is rarely camped and, even if it is, its generally by a quadder.  I just organise to grab 4 or 5 specific birds (round the ramp if I can) and let the quadder take the rest.  Have occasionally teamed up with quadders to kill the lightbringer.<br>
<br>
Loot is not great - individual birds can drop up to 6pp in cash, with pages, words and runes being the other drops.<br>
<br>
Pets?  I use 53 air with a suit of summoned armour.  Burn it out, ds it, use the 24 shock of swords to pull the bird, then let Jobaber solo it.  He might lose 10-15% health on a single proven, less with lightfeet and watchers.  Doing this I can pull constantly, even allowing for updating pet buffs and occasional 52 heals.  I can control up to 6 spawn spots before the first has repopped.  It's the constant pulling of all the birds that brings in the experience here, not just pulling the provens.  <br>
<br>
Boring...sometimes yes.  But I made 54 in 5 nights at about 2 to 3 hours a night.<br>
