<br>
Personally, at 54, I did the following: Neriak wizards (never camped anymore), JPF dryads, seafuries (no kidding, see below for why), JPF gnolls, soloed on WL side of Kael, and CS.  Of all of them, I found the JPF dryads to be the easiest/best xp.  I'm still doing them at 56.<br>
<br>
Seafuries... I found that I could keep up constant agro kiting with seafuries and my water pet.  Pull with one focused enhanced lava bolt at long range, set your pet on him with notaunt, when he gets below 20% pull another.  Your pet needs to have expedience on, and you'll need sow/jboots or a horse.  Make sure you have Scars memmed in case your pet gets agro.<br>
<br>
Once you get the idea, you can easily kite 4 at a time, just switching your pet to the next one as they die.  KEI is wonderful for keeping this going.<br>
<br>
Even though they were lt. blue, the xp of killing one every 45 seconds or so (what it takes for your water pet to go through them) adds up really, really, fast.  The hard part is actually regenning mana fast enough to keep up with your pet.  Heck, I still do this at 56 when I get bored of JPF.<br>
<br>
